Note:   To test the transformations, you need to first run the global to local
        transformations first, since the inverse test uses those results to
        transform back. They are also needed to perform the Cubit tests.
        You can run the tests by doing:

./test_global_to_local_multi.sh
./test_global_to_local_single.sh
./test_local_to_global_multi.sh
./test_local_to_global_single.sh
./test_local_to_cubit_global_multi.sh
./test_local_to_cubit_global_single.sh
./test_local_to_cubit_local_multi.sh
./test_local_to_cubit_local_single.sh

After running the tests, you can generate the meshes using Cubit by moving
into one of the Cubit output directories, e.g.,
../data/cfm-multi-global-cubit. For multi-fault tests, a master journal
file is created (master_local_to_cubit.jou). All of the fault meshes
may be generated within Cubit by just running this file.
